theorem interior_closure_eq_self_iff_open_of_closed
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} (hClosed : IsClosed A) :
    interior (closure A) = A ↔ IsOpen A := by
  -- `closure A` coincides with `A` because `A` is closed.
  have h_cl : closure A = A := hClosed.closure_eq
  constructor
  · intro hEq
    -- `interior (closure A)` is open; rewrite using `hEq`.
    have hOpenInt : IsOpen (interior (closure A)) := isOpen_interior
    simpa [hEq] using hOpenInt
  · intro hOpen
    -- From openness we get `interior A = A`; rewrite using `h_cl`.
    have hInt : interior A = A := hOpen.interior_eq
    simpa [h_cl] using hInt

theorem P2_iff_P3_and_interior_closure_eq
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P2 A ↔
      (Topology.P3 A ∧ interior (closure A) = interior (closure (interior A))) := by
  constructor
  · intro hP2
    have hP3 : Topology.P3 A := Topology.P2_implies_P3 hP2
    have hEq : interior (closure A) = interior (closure (interior A)) :=
      interior_closure_eq_closure_interior_of_P2 (A := A) hP2
    exact And.intro hP3 hEq
  · rintro ⟨hP3, hEq⟩
    dsimp [Topology.P2]
    intro x hxA
    have hxInt : x ∈ interior (closure A) := hP3 hxA
    simpa [hEq] using hxInt
